div.p:
The nineteenth Gojam;
                     Erroneouſly Goyame in the Mapps. Worſe Goroma by Godignus. Lib. 1. cap. 4. pag. 15.
                      pronounce it with the French, Gojam. A Kingdom wonderful for its ſituation, and famous for the Fountains of Nile therein now diſcovered. For the River Nile almoſt ſurrounds it in manner of a Peninſula. But that it cannot poſſibly be the Iſland of Meroe, as Tellezius believes, we ſhall prove in our Commentary. Godignus affirms, that it contains twenty Provinces, but conceals their Names.
